		<td><b>Re: Ayla <span class="posthilit">sprite</span> demo: overlap sprites for more colors</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Yeah, that was about alternating between two sprites to get more colors through the checkerboard pattern, but apparently that technique outright doesn't work properly at all due to how the NES generates the video signal (lots of color interference, and also the half-dot shenanigans).<br /><br />I think slobu is talking about using a solid <span class="posthilit">sprite</span> that flickers. That isn't prone to those issues... but flickering is noticeable no matter how hard you try. A good example of this would be the shield in Sonic 2, it's blatantly obvious it's flickering even at the speed it goes.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


